---
---


  <div class="min-h-screen bg-background pt-16 pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">
          Download <span class="text-primary">Coders in Flow</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-text-secondary">Get started with the most powerful AI coding assistant</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-surface rounded-2xl shadow-2xl overflow-hidden">
        <div class="bg-primary p-6 text-text-inverse">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">VS Code Extension</h2>
          <p class="text-text-inverse/90">Install directly from the Visual Studio Code Marketplace</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="p-8">
          <div class="mb-8">
            <a 
              href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=DarkFlows.codersinflow"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="block w-full bg-primary text-text-inverse text-center py-4 px-6 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg hover:bg-primary/90 transition-all duration-200 shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl"
            >
              Install from VS Code Marketplace
            </a>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-sm text-center mt-3">Opens in a new tab</p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-8 pt-8 border-t border-border">
            <h3 class="text-text-primary font-semibold mb-4">Installation Instructions:</h3>
            
            <div class="space-y-6">
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-link font-medium mb-2">Method 1: Install from Marketplace Website</h4>
                <ol class="text-text-secondary space-y-2 text-sm ml-4">
                  <li>1. Click the button above to open the marketplace page</li>
                  <li>2. Click the "Install" button on the marketplace page</li>
                  <li>3. VS Code will open and prompt you to install the extension</li>
                  <li>4. Click "Install" in VS Code to complete the installation</li>
                </ol>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-link font-medium mb-2">Method 2: Install from within VS Code</h4>
                <ol class="text-text-secondary space-y-2 text-sm ml-4">
                  <li>1. Open Visual Studio Code</li>
                  <li>2. Click the Extensions icon in the Activity Bar (or press <code class="bg-surface-hover px-2 py-1 rounded">Cmd+Shift+X</code> on Mac, <code class="bg-surface-hover px-2 py-1 rounded">Ctrl+Shift+X</code> on Windows/Linux)</li>
                  <li>3. Search for "Coders In Flow"</li>
                  <li>4. Click "Install" on the extension by DarkFlows</li>
                </ol>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-link font-medium mb-2">Method 3: Quick Install via Command Palette</h4>
                <ol class="text-text-secondary space-y-2 text-sm ml-4">
                  <li>1. Open VS Code</li>
                  <li>2. Press <code class="bg-surface-hover px-2 py-1 rounded">Cmd+P</code> (Mac) or <code class="bg-surface-hover px-2 py-1 rounded">Ctrl+P</code> (Windows/Linux)</li>
                  <li>3. Type: <code class="bg-surface-hover px-2 py-1 rounded">ext install DarkFlows.codersinflow</code></li>
                  <li>4. Press Enter to install</li>
                </ol>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 bg-primary/10 border border-primary/30 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-link text-sm mb-2">
              <strong>Requirements:</strong>
            </p>
            <ul class="text-link text-sm ml-4 space-y-1">
              <li>• Visual Studio Code version 1.70.0 or higher</li>
              <li>• Active internet connection for AI features</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 text-center">
        <a href="/" class="text-link hover:text-link-hover">← Back to Home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

